Git Internal Working
How Git Stores Data

Git stores everything as:

snapshots
hashes
objects

Each commit has:

unique SHA id
author
message
timestamp
What is Branch?

A branch is a separate line of development.

Advantage

Developers can work independently.

What is Merge?

Merge combines changes from one branch into another.

What is Clone?

Clone means copying a remote repository to local machine.

What is Pull?

Pull means:

fetch + merge

Downloads latest changes and updates local project.

What is Push?

Push uploads local commits to remote repository.

